         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: if (the mind) is well protected, [some] people</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: the <hi>cittavarga</hi> is finished [TB]: the [verse] collection on the mind (is finished)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: who is self supporting and not dependent on others</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: for him there is no reason for (mutterings) towards people</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB]: uncontrolled beings (strike) with words</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB]: hearing (a harsh word uttered)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht2375c"/>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>430-432</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>133</citedRange></bibl></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.31.60c <hi>citte tu surakṣite prajā</hi></note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.31.60end <hi>cittavargaḥ</hi>, here <hi>cittavargaḥ samāptaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.32.1b <hi>hy ātmabharāya hi nānyapoṣiṇe</hi>; lines Uv. 32.1b and 2b are identical, but line 1b fits better to the interval between a2 and a3.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">Uv.32.3d <hi>hy artho nāsti janasya lāpanam</hi> (see also <bibl><title corresp="ref:swft1973"/></bibl> IV: 58a; <bibl><title corresp="ref:strong1902"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.32.4a <hi>tudanti vācābhir asaṃyatā janāḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.32.4c <hi>śrutvā tu vācāṃ paruṣām udīritām</hi></note></p>
